Packet Sniffing Intro (Beginner Level)
# What is Packet Sniffing?
Packet Sniffing = capturing and analyizing network traffic
**Think: You're watching data travel across a network in real time
ex. When you run: ping google.com
Packets are sent from machine, travel across network, and come back
sniffer lets you see those packets
# Why this matters
Packet sniffing is used for:
detecting attacks
analyzing malware
troubleshooting networks
spying on traffic (if unencrypted)

use tcpdump to capture packets and observe ICMP traffic when pinging Google

**HTTP -> readable traffic
HTTPS -> encrypted (can't read)

# Commands
sudo tcpdump -> captures arll the traffic
sudo tcpdump -> capture ping traffic
sudo tcpdump host <ip> -> filter by IP

Key Idea: Packets show how data is moved across networks
